Dec 4 2004	Great location and adequate service...great price too!	We stayed at the Hotel Oliver for three nights in late November 2004. The location at Earls Court is great. Easy access to the tube, right on the line direct from Heathrow too! The hotel was clean, the staff was courteous and helpful. The room was what we would expect in England, small, but adequate. The bed was a little bit hard and uncomfortable, but we weren't in Englnd to sleep anyway. The best improvement I could have asked for is a more comfortable bed, but considering all else, location, price, and staff I really can't complain. The included breakfast included either cereal or a hard boiled egg, tea or coffee, and toast with jam and an apple. We will consider the Hotel Oliver again when we return to London.	
